        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 6:44AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 644 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 3 miles west of Ozark to near Hackett. Movement
was east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Charleston...                     Dyer...
Kibler...                         Central City...
Cameron...                        Panama...
Vesta...                          Ursula...
Mulberry...                       Altus...
Greenwood...                      Alix...
Bloomer...                        Hackett...
Meg...                            Barling...
Midland...                        Bonanza...
Jenson...                         Burnville...

This includes the following highways,
Interstate 40 in Arkansas between mile markers 21 and 25.
Interstate 540 between mile markers 8 and 14.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 AM CDT for northwestern
and west central Arkansas...and southeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
